\begin_layout Standard
This chapter formally introduced a new optimization problem for 3G networks:
 the SHO-balancing problem.
 A characterization of the consequences that unbalanced SHO areas have on
 the quality of HSPA services was also given.
 Particularly, tackling the SHO-balancing problem was possible due to the
 improved performance delivered by the evaluation framework PRATO (see Chapter
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


